  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 65533c272dfcf054691c17408835c52c, type: 3}
  m_Name: HowToMakeMorePuzzles
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  documentation: "1)Create a scriptable object clue data for any clues you plan to
    use.  Asign a 2d sprite to represent it on board, and choose hovewer many tags
    you want the player to recive when picking it up\n\n2)Chose 3d objects to serve
    as clues to find, add a clue script to them, put any number of clueData that
    this object represents.\n\nOptonaly: add aditional objects to be inspectablt
    by adding an InspectableObject script\n\nNote that both sripts require a collider
    and will refuse to be added to objects without one to prevent erorrs\n\n3)Create
    as many solution scripatble objects as the amount of specific connections you
    want to have, for each one assign two clue data files to represent the clues
    and chosse a tag that needs to connect them. \n\nThten depending on the goal
    of the puzzle either put all the solutions in a list on the default solution
    checher in the scene if you want solving the puzzle to end the level or create
    another solution checher objet using the namesake script and assign the desired
    effect to its on SolutionCorrect event"
